#: ../../../news.rst:64
msgid ""
"Add :ref:`template strings queries <template-strings>` (:ticket:`#1054`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:65
msgid ""
"More flexible :ref:`composite adaptation<adapt-composite>`: it is now "
"possible to adapt Python objects to PostgreSQL composites and back even if "
"they are not sequences or if they take keyword arguments (:ticket:`#932`, :"
"ticket:`#1202`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:68
msgid ""
"Cursors are now iterators_, not just iterables_. This means you can call "
"`next`\\ ``(cur)`` or `anext`\\ ``(cur)``, which is useful as a :ref:`type-"
"safe expression <typing-fetchone>` (:ticket:`#1064`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:71
msgid ""
"Add `Cursor.set_result()` and `Cursor.results()` to move across the result "
"sets of queries executed though `~Cursor.executemany()` or `~Cursor."
"execute()` with multiple statements (:tickets:`#1080, #1170`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:74
msgid ""
"Add :ref:`transaction-status` to report the status during and after a "
"`~Connection.transaction()` block (:ticket:`#969`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:76
msgid ""
"Allow to change loaders using `~adapt.AdaptersMap.register_loader()` on "
"`Cursor.adapters` after a query result has been already returned (:ticket:"
"`#884`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:81 ../../../news.rst:305
msgid "New libpq wrapper features"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:82
msgid ""
"Add `pq.PGconn.used_gssapi` attribute and `Capabilities.has_used_gssapi()` "
"function (:ticket:`#1138`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:84
msgid ""
"Add `ConnectionInfo.full_protocol_version` attribute, `Capabilities."
"has_full_protocol_version()` function (:ticket:`#1079`)."
msgstr ""

